snippet.textDisplay: I’ve done this before, but easier, you take the ice cream and in order to shape the ice cream easier you can wrap it with plastic so it’s not nasty on the hands, and before covering it with corn flakes you flat wonder bread and you cover the ice cream with a nice layer of flattened wonder bread, which covers the ice cream so it’s easier to fry. Then you leave it in the freezer all night, and then proceed to deep fry by covering the ball of wonder bread - ice cream. This protects the ice cream and gives it an amazing crunchy layer. You can use tempura mixture to easily coat the ice cream ball which will make it sticky enough to cover it with corn flakes :)
snippet.textOriginal: I’ve done this before, but easier, you take the ice cream and in order to shape the ice cream easier you can wrap it with plastic so it’s not nasty on the hands, and before covering it with corn flakes you flat wonder bread and you cover the ice cream with a nice layer of flattened wonder bread, which covers the ice cream so it’s easier to fry. snippet.textDisplay:
You can actually do this without frying it! This is how you do it like they do at mexican restaurants (and me!)...
*roll ice cream, put in freezer
*use a food processor to crush up Frosted Flakes and mix in cinnamon
*take Ice cream out, roll them in the frosted flakes
*drizzle honey all over the ice cream
*put ice cream back in freezer for an hour or as long as you want.
VOILA IT'S FREAKIN DELICIOUS, EASY, AND NO FRYING NECESSARY!
snippet.textOriginal:
